Here, we will keep tab on the current element in the variable 'now'. And we are keeping a counter to count the number of elements with the value 'now'.

If the count becomes more than 2, we will remove that element from the list. 

Time complexity: O(n)
Space complexity: O(1)

**Code:**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int removeDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
        int now,count=1,pos=1;
        now=nums[0];
        for(int i=pos;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i]==now){
                count++;
                if(count>2){
                    nums.erase(nums.begin()+i);
                    i--;
                }
            }
            else {
                    count=1;
                    now=nums[i];
            }
        }
        return nums.size();
    }
};
```

